psi.cache

Interface PsiCacheProvider


  • public interface PsiCacheProvider
    An interface representing a key-value cache used by the sdk to store the results of heavyweight mathematical operations (such as encryption operations), which can be read in subsequent executions with the same inputs to speed up the execution. Since the goal of the cache is to reduce the computational time with respect to running the actual computations, reading and writing to the cache should be relatively lightweight. When the cache is enabled, the sdk performs concurrent calls to the caching layer. Consequently, the implementations of this interface should be thread safe.

      • get

        java.util.Optional<java.lang.String> get(java.lang.String key)
        Gets the value associated to the input key.
        Parameters:
        key - the key whose associated value is returned
        Returns:
        an Optional containing the cached value to which the specified key is mapped, or Optional.empty() if the cache contains no mapping for the key

      • put

        void put(java.lang.String key,
         java.lang.String value)
        If the specified key is not present in the cache, stores it with the passed value. If it is already present, do nothing.
        Parameters:
        key - key of the cache entry
        value - value of the cache entry associated to the key
